From 89f26628b6457d632fa6b9b2817d5610d77eca6d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: radhevrishi <radhev.232@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 11:22:10 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 05/17] fix(earnings): remove Div Yield, US concall upload, EPS
 YoY fallback
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three small follow-ups gathered during user testing:

 - Drop the Div Yield tile from India Profitability & Leverage. User
   doesn't track it and it crowds the row.
 - Wire onConcallText through to InstitutionalReport too so US tickers
   (Tesla et al.) get the same paste-transcript modal that India just
   gained. handleUsConcallText reruns buildSnapshot with the cached
   FinancialsInput / estimates / history JSON so we don't re-hit FMP.
 - Tesla's EPS YoY column showed '—' because EDGAR XBRL only fills
   epsBasic for the current quarter — fin.epsPrior was always null.
   Fall back to history[4].eps (same fiscal quarter one year ago) so
   the YoY surprise number actually renders. Same fix applied to
   revenue YoY for symmetry, even though FMP usually fills revPrior.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
